<title type="html"><![CDATA[$5800 in MMC5]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3350&amp;p=24022#p24022"><![CDATA[
Yeah, I saw that page in the wiki as well as the patent before, and the two seem to sync up for the most part, although the details are very sketchy (as is to be expected when reading patent gibberish).  What we need is hardware testing - has anyone investigated $5010 yet?<br /><br />An easy test that wouldn't require hearing MMC5 sound output would be to set $5010 to 1 and read a byte in $8000-BFFF that's set to zero.  If the patent is correct, that should trigger an IRQ (acknowledged in $5010.D7).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=360">dvdmth</a> — Sun May 06, 2007 9:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
